description:
&lt;p&gt;The Princess Alexandra Hospital Harlow is actively seeking to recruit a Radiographer to join our dynamic team providing a high standard of care to all patients and contributing to the overall efficiency and effectiveness of the Radiology department.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;WE ALSO WOULD WELCOME APPLICATIONS FROM CANDIDATES INTERESTED IN SPECIALISING IN NUCLEAR MEDICINE (FULL TRAINING WILL BE GIVEN- WITH THE OPPORTUNITY FOR POST GRADUATE CERTIFICATION). PLEASE REFERENCE YOUR INTEREST IN THE APPLICATION.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It’s an exciting time to join the Radiology Department, this is a new post created due to service expansion and the successful candidate will be actively involved with new developments and innovations within the specialty of radiology and help to promote change.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role will cover all of the duties expected of a band 6 Radiographer. You will also be responsible for the supervision of Assistant Practitioners and Undergraduate Student Radiographers&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The department provides 24/7 cover for emergencies and operates a 7 day working rota, so candidates will be expected to cover any 7.5 hour or 12 hour shift between 8am-8pm. Weekday night shifts are also part of the standard rota. Participation in the on-call rota will also be expected.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The main acute site is PAH, however there are imaging departments at St Margaret&#39;s Hospital in Epping and Herts &amp; Essex hospital in Bishops Stortford and staff are required to work at these sites.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For this role you will need to be:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Qualified and HCPC Registered Radiographer, Competent organisational and prioritisation skills, Ability to work as part of a team. Excellent verbal and written communication skills. Patient orientated, attitude reflecting PAH Trust Values. Demonstrate ability to work under pressure and concentrate on tasks in a busy environment. Pleasant and professional manner. Customer Service experience&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameElizabeth PennJob titleRadiology Clinical ManagerTelephone number01279 827074&lt;/p&gt;
